md:titleInfo.md:title: Taltīf al-mizāğ min ši'r Ibn al-Hağğāğ
Taltīf al-mizāğ min ši'r Ibn al-Hağğāğ

md:note.div:
Ibn al-Hağğāğ al-Baġdādī var en populær digter kendt for sine respektløse sukhf-digte.
Samlingen er udvalgt af Ibn Nubātah al-Misrī (d. 768 H [1366])
Håndskriftet er købt i Kairo i 1763 af den danske filolog Frederik Christian von Haven (d. 1763), medlem af Carsten Niebuhr ekspeditionen (1761-1767).
Cod. Arab. 260

Ibn al-Hağğāğ al-Baġdādī was a popular poet famous for his irreverent sukhf-verses.
The anthology is selected by Ibn Nubātah al-Misrī (d. 768 H [1366 CE])
The manuscript was bought in Cairo in 1763 by the Danish philologist Frederik Christian von Haven (d. 1763 CE), a member of the Carsten Niebuhr expedition (1761-1767 CE).
Cod. Arab. 260
